tic field is affected by previous tests, so consistency is key.\n1877:[thinking] I’m considering including in the same test a call using `JspTag.class` followed by `SimpleTagSupport.class`. If the coverage is still lacking, that would be puzzling. Perhaps there's an initialization step at build time? I could try adding a test that uses `SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass` with an invalid `Object.class`. It seems to call `class$` but returns null. This approach seems simpler, without needing a parent chain. I think I’ll add the first assertion to keep it straightforward and less setup-intensive.\n1881:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"public class SimpleTagSupportTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void findAncestorWithClassFindsSimpleTagParent() {\\n        SimpleTagSupport parent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, SimpleTagSupport.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"newText\":\"public class SimpleTagSupportTest {\\n    @Test\\n    public void findAncestorWithClassChecksJspTagTypeBeforeWalkingParents() {\\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    public void findAncestorWithClassFindsSimpleTagParentByInterface() {\\n        SimpleTagSupport parent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, JspTag.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}]}\n1882:[tool-call] end id=call_JcPeM9KjEMvhEKtgqLsMYCA7|fc_0e4d82b4dd45a7230169f51429d8048192b6f7bbc