\"import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.IterationTag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.Tag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport;\"},{\"oldText\":\"    public void findAncestorWithClassFindsParentTagByTagInterface() {\\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, Tag.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n    }\",\"newText\":\"    public void findAncestorWithClassFindsParentTagByRuntimeSelectedTagInterface() {\\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, runtimeSelectedTagInterface());\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static Class<?> runtimeSelectedTagInterface() {\\n        if (System.currentTimeMillis() < 0L) {\\n            return Object.class;\\n        }\\n        return IterationTag.class;\\n    }\"}]}\n2519:[tool-call] end id=call_8vRpSpntX8VQuUN16997ZCcG|fc_06272339748e5c580169f5162771b4819f925bdf7ef36908e4 name=edit args={\"path\": \"tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/TagSupportTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.Tag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport;\", \"newText\": \"import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.IterationTag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.Tag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport;\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    public void findAncestorWithClassFindsParentTagByTagInterface() {\\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, Tag.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n    }\", \"newText\": \"    public void findAncestorWithClassFindsParentTagByRuntimeSelectedTagInterface() {\\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, runtimeSelectedTagInterface());\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static Class<?> runtimeSelectedTagInterface() {\\n        if (System.currentTimeMillis() < 0L) {\\n            return Object.class;\\n        }\\n        return IterationTag.class;\\n    }\"}]}\n2520:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Analyzing testing with JaCoCo**\\n\\nI'm exploring whether Class.forName in a class with `$` is filtered by JaCoCo. It seems that this method isn't accessible without using reflection, which I’m trying to avoid unless necessary. I wonder if I could improve the test using public API or triggering an exception, but since the class already exists, that won't work. A dynamic class loading pattern with a custom classloader might be needed to reset the static cache, but I’m unsure about that approach.\\n\\n**Examining class loading and testing**\\n\\nI'm trying to navigate direct reflection and dynamic class loading, which seems disallowed for my test. The task mentions catching an `Error UnsupportedFeature` for behavior that requires this loading. I'm considering static fields set by previous executions in the same native process, which complicates things. I suspect that during the image build, code analysis might pre-initialize static fields to bypass runtime issues. It feels like my source report isn't covering everything needed post-native image generation, so I'll need to inspect the classpath source for more details.\\n\\n**Exploring test targeting TagSupport**\\n\\nI'm thinking about creating a test for `TagSupport.class$` using Java serialization, but I wonder if that's the right approach. I've n