tatic fields set by previous executions in the same native process, which complicates things. I suspect that during the image build, code analysis might pre-initialize static fields to bypass runtime issues. It feels like my source report isn't covering everything needed post-native image generation, so I'll need to inspect the classpath source for more details.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring test targeting TagSupport**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about creating a test for `TagSupport.class$` using Java serialization, but I wonder if that's the right approach. I've noted that the `findAncestorWithClass` method in `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport` has conditions that trigger a class literal if `from` or `klass` are non-null. Since I’ve already tested with those cases, I’m considering adding an `Object.class` call with a parent. This might be useful if the compiler optimizes to branch away from `Tag.class`. I’ll have to explore this further!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Ensuring proper class usage**\\\\n\\\\nI need to use `currentTimeMillis`, but I must ensure that I pass `IterationTag.class` and not `Tag.class`. Even if the compiler can recognize both classes as objects and prove their compatibility, it still requires the right condition. I'm curious if the internal class call could be optimized in some way. I want to make sure I'm getting this detail right! It's all about precision and understanding the nuances of class handling.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_8vRpSpntX8VQuUN16997ZCcG|fc_06272339748e5c580169f5162771b4819f925bdf7ef36908e4\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/TagSupportTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.Tag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport;\", \"newText\": \"import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.IterationTag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.