}`.\n3134:  forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:4:> [Dynamic-access strategy](dynamic-access-strategy.md)\n3135:  forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:39:        DAReport[(\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\")]\n3137:  forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:167:- **Loop**: parses `dynamic-access-coverage.json`; iterates over classes with\n3144:  forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:12:Full dynamic-access coverage report, all classes with uncovered call sites:\n3145:  forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:17:- Keep coverage for each dynamic-access class in its own dedicated `{test_language_display_name}` test file under `src/test/{test_source_dir_name}` in `graalvm-reachability-metadata`.\n3148:  forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:11:**dynamic-access call site** reported by the reachability repo's coverage tool\n3157:  forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:180:A missing or unparsable `dynamic-access-coverage.json` after the initial\n3158:  forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:198:2. The dynamic-access coverage report is regenerated **after** exploration so\n3167:  forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:72:            \"even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\n3169:  tests/src/org.lz4/lz4-java/1.8.0/src/test/java/org_lz4/lz4_java/LZ4FactoryTest.java:38:                + \"lz4 factory dynamic access coverage\")\n3170:  tests/src/org.lz4/lz4-java/1.8.0/src/test/java/org_lz4/lz4_java/XXHashFactoryTest.java:36:                + \"xxhash factory dynamic access coverage\")\n3171:  tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org_jboss_logmanager/jboss_logmanager/Formatters12Test.java:51:                \"Anonymous privileged-action construction is only needed for JVM dynamic-access coverage\");\n3172:  tests/src/org.iq80.snappy/snappy/0.5/src/test/java/org_iq80_snappy/snappy/SnappyInternalUtilsTest.java:59:        byte[] phrase = \"snappy dynamic access coverage payload \".