he standard `basic_iterative` strategy automatically.\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:440:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:447:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:469:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1768:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1784:    covered_calls = int(dynamic_access.get(\\\"coveredCalls\\\", 0) or 0)\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1798:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1809:        \\\"dynamic-access\\\",\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1810:        \\\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\\\",\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1815:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1942:        \\\"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1946:        \\\"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\\\n\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1965:        f\\\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1967:        \\\"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1969:        \\\"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\\\n\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2631:            pipeline_argv.append(\\\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\\\")\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4537:        \\\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\\\",\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4540:            \\\"Forwarded to the new-library p