namic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:572:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:592:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:593:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:614:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:615:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:636:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:637:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:658:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:659:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:697:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:715:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:728:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Library-update strategy: skips primary workflow, directly runs dynamic-access coverage improvement on existing tests.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:733:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_improve_coverage.py:73:This PR improves dynamic-access coverage for {coordinates} by generating additional tests.\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` 